snippet.textDisplay: Have literally been here since the very beginning when you did meal preps, and grocery hauls out of your apartment off campus. Once you created your own little private gym, then a few articles of clothing, I was hooked. I remember you shipping first clothing orders out of your parents home. And I remember just how supportive your parents were, especially Senora Guzman(seeing her here made me choke up). I also remember your early sponsorships, and your vision to have a larger gym, then an even larger gym where exercise conscious individuals like myself could get a decent workout. I remember when you bought your first house, and I remember more cars and trucks that even the common person couldn't even fathom acquiring. I also remember when you'd have those impromptu moments on camera about your dreams and plans for the future. (This is why I kept coming back to your YouTube channel). And I remember seeing your clothing brand expand exponentially. In the very beginning I always defended your vision CG here on your channel. And I still do today. Yes there is a part of your past that I miss seeing, but sometimes in life good things have to fall away, so that better things can fall into place. Man, you got this!

snippet.textDisplay: Amazing inspiring video. People will always tell you it is a bad idea dropping out of school, but a degree is just a degree. Me and my husband are busy with our own brand, online stores. We work very very hard, nobody learned us in school how to build a website, how to start a brand. We are 1.2 years busy with building and creating a new life, we sold products so we know it works. Right now, we are not doing well. But we believe in our brand, and we have seen that people want our products many times. But all that we want is to build a brand and be recognized, work for ourself. It’s not so much about they money, if it would be about money we could do something else. Always believe in yourself and ‘don’t let the tamed once’s tell you how to life’. I am battling a burnout and a depression right now. But, i will come back way way stronger. I believe we are capable of achieving anything. Christian, this is amazing, so proud of you. I watched you become a man, i am an first vlog watcher. I am so excited for you!
